<TEXT>
graffiti has become such a scourge in 
warsaw that city authorities intend to erect walls where people can 
scrawl whatever they please without fear of censorship a spokesman 
for the mayor says 
in poland graffiti usually carries a political message and is 
most often quickly painted over by authorities with dull hues that 
accentuate the eyesore 
graffiti and other vandalism cost the city more than 18 million 
last year and slogans scrawled during a happening friday near 
warsaws main department store caused 9000 in damage authorities 
say 
municipal officials decided monday to build the freespeech 
graffiti walls at locations still to be decided said zbigniew 
kopka the mayors spokesman 
everyone will have a chance to express themselves if only the 
paint is no longer sprayed on the walls of our buildings or 
underground passageways he said tuesday 
scrawling on walls has a long tradition in poland 
a crossandanchor symboly with the initials pw for poland 
is fighting became a national symbol of resistance during world 
war ii 
</TEXT>
