<TEXT>
the merce cunningham dance company opened its 
season at the city center on tuesday with the premiere of five 
stone wind and the choreographer himself was among the dancers 
for much of this 55minute work the stage is full of dancers but 
all are motionless except one or two the primary motif consists of 
standing on one foot while stretching bending and rotating the 
other leg 
this is not a dance that flows there are many entrances and 
exits from five different points only occasionally do dancers move 
in unison or as duet partners 
cunningham who will turn 70 in april does arm stretches bends 
and turns usually in the back of the group once on stage alone 
one would expect him to look silly among his trim young dancers 
but he fits the tone of the dance and makes one think about the 
effectiveness of one or two more mature dancers in the bunch 
cunningham is inventive enough even pursuing one choreographic 
idea to keep one interested throughout also we like long dances 
so the evening isnt spent mainly in intermissions between short 
dances still we became restless before the end 
costumes are leotard tops and skirts or pants later leotards 
only for the women in varying colors chosen by mark lancaster the 
score was created by john cage takehisa kosugi and david tudor and 
has a few painfully loud bursts of sound 
the first part of five stone wind had its premier in berlin 
last june the complete work bowed at the festival davignon in 
france in july 
