<TEXT>
senate clean air supporters have promised to 
write a tough new antipollution bill by july 4 an announcement 
made while environmental experts were telling a house panel that 
healthy adults and children are now at risk from dirty air 
the house energy and commerce health subcommittee was told 
tuesday that the nation faces a health emergency with 150 million 
americans now living in areas with unsafe levels of ozone and carbon 
monoxide 
dr philip j landrigan representing the american academy of 
pediatrics and the american public health association said children 
are especially vulnerable to air pollution because their airways are 
more narrow than those of adults and because of their increased 
frequency of respiratory infections 
he said studies of children in summer camps show those exposed to 
ozone at concentrations even below current allowable levels 
developed temporary respiratory problems 
childrens often high levels of activity put them at risk for 
acute respiratory effects due to ozone exposure landrigan said 
dr thomas godar representing the american lung association 
said americans mistakenly accept dirty air as one of the facts of 
life 
ozone can cause immediate shortterm changes in lung function 
and increased respiratory symptoms in healthy adults and children 
who exercise moderately or heavily during periods of elevated ozone 
concentrations he said 
significant decreases in lung function and symptoms such as 
coughing and pain are experienced by exercising individuals 
exposed to ozone for one to two hours at levels comparable to those 
frequently found in unsafe air quality areas he said 
sen max baucus dmont who will sponsor the senates clean air 
bill this year announced that sections of the legislation will be 
introduced at these time intervals toxic air pollutants april 3 
new air quality standards including controls on auto emissions may 
1 and acid rain control june 1 
