prime minister rajiv gandhis government 
has slashed defense spending and diverted funds to fight hunger 
illiteracy and provide homes for the homeless 
the unprecedented reduction in defense spending was contained in 
the governments budget for 198990 introduced in parliament on 
tuesday by finance minister shankarrao b chavan 
gandhis government reacted to criticism that it is oriented 
toward the rich by pledging to reduce official expenditures and 
slapping new levies on cars televisions electronic goods air 
travel and hotel tariffs 
analysts said the budget was aimed at wooing the electorate most 
of them the rural poor 
gandhi came to power in 1984 after the assassination of his 
mother and predecessor indira gandhi under indian law he is 
required to call national elections by the end of the year 
india will spend 2 billion rupees 133 million less on defense 
in the 198990 fiscal year compared to the previous years expenses 
chavan said 
indias armed forces with the sixth largest army in the world 
has 13 million soldiers 
