<TEXT>
hungarys electronic alarm system along 
its border with austria will be dismantled by january 1991 partly 
because of too many false alarms official reports said wednesday 
a report submitted to the communist partys politburo said 
guarding the borders poses a growing burden for guards thanks to 
the fact that hungarys ties with the world have expanded the 
government news agency reported 
in an interview published in the government newspaper magyar 
hirlap the commander of the western hungary border zone said the 
guards wholeheartedly support the initiative it is an outdated 
system 
col istvan franko quoted the guards as saying the technical 
warning system posed a physical and mental stress for them 
franko said that in the sopron border region alone 4374 alarms 
were registered last year of which only 44 were actual border 
violations 
ninetythree percent of the violations were committed by foreign 
citizens mainly east germans heading for austria 
