<TEXT>
a trial began wednesday for 253 people charged with 
insurrection during the reign of leftist terror in italy during the 
1970s and early 1980s 
several defendants including noted red brigade members such as 
barbara balzerani were convicted in the 1978 kidnapping and murder 
of former prime minister aldo moro another noted defendant is 
renato curcio who headed the red brigade during the height of its 
activity 
if convicted on charges of insurrection and civil war the 
defendents face sentences of life imprisonment 
about 40 defendants watched the opening proceedings from inside 
steelbarred cages another 40 who are jailed refused to attend the 
proceedings exercising their right under italian law to skip their 
own trial 
many have renounced terrorism but some vowed from their 
courtroom cells to support the struggle of comrades in the red 
army faction the west germanbased leftist terrorist movement 
the italian government says it has practically eradicated 
leftwing terrorist activity however terrorists have carried out 
spectacular crimes in recent years including the 1988 slaying of an 
italian senator at his home 
</TEXT>
