violations including fabricating high school diplomas for recruits 
a newspaper reported today 
the pittsburgh press quoted marine maj robert w mclean a corps 
spokesman at parris island sc as saying that six of the 
recruiters face courtsmartial on charges that will be filed within 
the next few weeks 
punishment for the nine others ranged from forfeiture of pay to 
letters of reprimand he said 
investigators found recruiters provided as many as 17 diplomas 
for recruits who never graduated from high school the newspaper 
said 
in addition the criminal records of some recruits were omitted 
from enlistment papers as were medical problems that could have 
disqualified recruits from serving the press said 
the investigation began in january after a suburban pittsburgh 
recruit became ill at boot camp on parris island and had to be 
hospitalized for a severe ulcer his mother says she reported to the 
recruiter the newspaper said 
investigators later identified 82 others who may have been 
recruited improperly 
