suspected of killing him officials said wednesday 
the murder of undercover special agent everette hatcher on 
tuesday was the first killing of a drug enforcement administration 
officer in the new york area since 1972 said dea spokesman robert 
strang 
the dea fbi and police issued an allpoints bulletin for 
constible gus farace 28 of staten island 
farace was released from the elmira correction facility in june 
1988 after serving eight years for the 1979 kidnapping and murder of 
a new jersey teenager said police sources who spoke on the 
condition of anonymity 
