<TEXT>
telemedia inc canadas largest publisher of 
consumer magazines said wednesday it has reached a tentative 
agreement to buy new england monthly a 5yearold regional magazine 
that has been struggling toward profitability 
terms of the sale were not disclosed pending ratification of the 
agreement by the magazines 59 shareholders robert nylen the 
publisher said the legal papers will be completed this week and the 
shareholders probably will vote before the end of march 
telemedia said both nylen 44 and the magazines editor daniel 
okrent 40 will continue in their jobs 
despite winning national awards for journalism and tripling its 
circulation to more than 116000 new england monthlys costs 
continue to exceed its revenues nylen said 
we started in 1984 and weve made progress in each subsequent 
year each year weve shaved our losses by several hundred thousand 
dollars and now were within striking distance of profitability 
nylen said 
the magazine based in haydenville mass has a staff of 40 and 
annual revenues of more than 4 million it won national magazine 
awards for general excellence in 1985 and 1986 
a literate breezy often irreverent publication new england 
monthly frequently profiles small companies or craftsmen and devotes 
one issue a year to local heroes but it has been harshly 
critical of some of new englands most powerful institutions and 
individuals recent issues for example have cast rhode islands 
leading families and massachusetts lotus development corp in an 
unflattering light 
approximately 6 million has been invested in the magazine since 
1984 and nylen said telemedia will inject a few million dollars 
more to keep it going 
i expect that the magazine will operate much as it has but it 
is not immutable nylen said what we really want is their 
advice and counsel and that may mean changes in marketing 
advertising or other areas 
stephen j weir telemedias vice president for finance said 
stockholders of the magazine will not receive any payment up front 
but will be paid over a period of years under a formula tied to new 
england monthlys future earnings he declined to comment on the 
potential size of the payments 
the shareholders include private investors venture capitalists 
and two british merchant banks 
telemedia incs other holdings include canadian television and 
radio stations the canadian edition of tv guide and harrowsmith 
magazine 
