exchange with the contract for delivery in march at 1455 a pound 
the highest settlement price for the march contract since jan 27 
but still well below the record high for spot copper of 16475 a 
pound reached dec 8 on the exchange 
the rally was sparked by news that miners in peru the worlds 
sixthlargest copper producer would consider extending a planned 
3day strike if conditions warrant the strike is scheduled to begin 
on march 26 
the reports stirred memories of last falls 57day peruvian 
mining strike which was a major factor in coppers rise to record 
price levels 
demand for copper remains strong and supplies continue to be 
tight a situation reflected in the slim number of delivery notices 
posted tuesday and wednesday on the exchange 
the delivery notices signify the intent of commercial traders to 
deliver copper against the march contract which expires on march 
29 a small number of delivery notices would indicate a reluctance 
or inability among copper processors to deliver the metal 
suggesting that their own supplies are limited 
only three delivery notices were issued tuesday the first notice 
day and none were posted on wednesday 
analysts said the markets bullish supplyanddemand factors and 
strong chart signals could lead to another run at record price 
levels 
its starting to look like a replay of 1987 and 1988 when 
copper prices reached their last two peaks said fred demler metals 
economist with drexel burnham lambert inc in new york 
