<TEXT>
amtrak will open the first major new 
rail route in its 18year history when it begins service to atlantic 
city on may 23 anticipating 14 million new riders a year 
officials announced wednesday 
the atlantic city express more commonly called the 
gamblers express will include five roundtrips on weekdays and 
several more roundtrips on the weekends said timothy p gardner 
amtraks vice president of marketing one direct line will originate 
in washington and another will start in new york he said 
amtrak has added new cities and frequencies to its existing rail 
network but never before created an entirely new route said amtrak 
spokesman john jacobsen 
nj transit has delayed commuter service on the rail line until 
1991 nj transit officials announced funding cutbacks tuesday to 
meet a projected budget deficit 
but gardner said nj transits delay would not affect amtraks 
start 
new jersey transit has been extremely cooperative in getting 
the physical plant assembled he said even if they end up 
postponing their commuter service for a year it will not affect 
our plans 
passenger service into the seaside resort was stopped in 1982 
because of low ridership and poor track conditions 
amtrak nj transit and the atlantic county improvement authority 
are sharing costs on the 101 million new rail project including 
repairing the old tracks and building a new atlantic city terminal 
and local stations 
amtrak expects to bring in revenue of about 30 million a year 
gardner said 
tentative amtrak fares include a 25 roundtrip charge between 
atlantic city and philadelphia a 49 roundtrip from washington 
and a 46 roundtrip from new york gardner said an express trip to 
new york would take 2 hours he said 
